\begin_layout Subsection
Save/Render/Increment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where / How is "Silently Increment Filenames..." stored?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the REAPER resource folder, open REAPER.ini and look for a line like this:
 Code:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
renderclosewhendone=4
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The auto-increment option is enabled when the value has bit &16 set, so
 if the option is disabled, add 16 to the value to enable it, and if it's
 enabled, subtract 16 from the value to disable it.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To set on the fly try the SNM_SetIntConfigVar() function (requires SWS extension
), https://mespotin.uber.space/Ultrasch...rclosewhendone
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Code:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
-- Enable Silently increment filenames enableOK = reaper.SNM_SetIntConfigVar("ren
derclosewhendone", reaper.SNM_GetIntConfigVar("renderclosewhendone", -666)|16)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Code:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
-- Disable Silently increment filenames disableOK = reaper.SNM_SetIntConfigVar("r
enderclosewhendone", reaper.SNM_GetIntConfigVar("renderclosewhendone", -666)&(~16
))
\end_layout

